description.narrative: UNICEF strengthened prevention, attention of victims and prosecution of off-line and on-line sexual exploitation against children through strengthening the capacities of the judicial and protection systems, to improve the coverage of services, to increase child protection, and to prosecute these crimes, in the framework of the National Roadmap on Violence Against Children. UNICEF supported the OGA and CONANI, to develop two integrated protocols for investigation and assistance of child sexual exploitation survivors, and to prevent CSE working with CSO and the private sector. UNICEF supported the design and implementation of the National Response against on-line sexual exploitation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/02/2020
